correctness.rationale: The extraction contains multiple factual errors, schema violations, and non-traceable/fabricated values. Key issues: (1) Growth-per-cycle: Values given as 115 and 40 ANGSTROM are incorrect; the article reports 115 and 40 ng/cm^2 per cycle, not thickness. GPC should be in length units (~1 Å/cycle for ZnO), not mass. (2) Dosing/purge times: Article uses 1 s and 20 s; schema unit is MilliSEC but numeric values are set to 1 and 20 (ms). They should be 1000 ms and 20000 ms. (3) Film thickness: Set to 0.7 nm, which in the article refers to the thickness difference between cases, not the total film thickness; total thickness for 220 cycles is not explicitly 0.7 nm. (4) MaterialDeposited: Listed as ZnO; the core process is Al-doped ZnO (ZnO:Al). (5) Supercycle/doping sequence: RD/Z=1/19 is captured, but the distinct doping sequences (case 1–3: TMA/H2O, TMA/DEZ/H2O, DEZ/TMA/H2O) are not encoded; subcycleSequence is too generic and misses the reported order effects. (6) Schema violations: Multiple fields set to None where the schema expects objects (plasmaPower, optical/electrical/device properties). These should be omitted if not reported. In addition, saturation, dosingTime, purgeTime, flowRates, and filmThickness are incorrectly nested under thicknessControl; per schema they belong at processParameters level (filmThickness also required there). (7) Flow rates: Values assigned (100 sccm for precursor/co-reactant, 10 sccm purge) are not supported by the text; 100 sccm is total flow and 10 sccm is for back-side Ar on the QCM, not precursor/co-reactant flows. Units used (SCM-PER-MIN) imply m^3/min and are inconsistent with sccm. (8) Film density: 5.675 entered with GM-PER-DeciM3 (g/L) rather than g/cm^3; also this was an assumed bulk value for conversion, not a measured film density by ellipsometry. (9) Composition: AtomicRatio ‘1:19’ (AES) confuses gas-cycle ratio with measured atomic ratio; elemental concentration 0.5% is not reported (0.5 at% is cited as sensitivity limit, not composition). (10) Crystallinity marked ‘amorphous’ (FTIR) is not supported for RD/Z=1/19; amorphous ZnAl2O4 features are discussed for heavy doping (RD/Z=1/4). (11) Uniformity (5%) and conformality (aspect ratio 1) are not reported and appear fabricated. (12) Optical properties: refractive index 1.95 is a modeling parameter for ellipsometry, not measured by FTIR as listed. Correct or remove these fields and realign all values with the article and schema.

completeness.rationale: Major omissions and schema/traceability violations. (1) Multiple processes are described in the article but only one was extracted. At minimum, separate processes should be created for: undoped ZnO; ZnO:Al for case 1 (TMA/H2O), case 2 (TMA/DEZ/H2O), and case 3 (DEZ/TMA/H2O) at RD/Z = 1/19; and additional runs at RD/Z = 1/9 and 1/4 (and SIMS sample at RD/Z = 1/39). (2) Growth-per-cycle is incorrect and not traceable: the article reports QCM mass uptake (115 and 40 ng/cm2 per cycle for ZnO and Al2O3), not thickness. The extraction wrongly records these as 115 and 40 Å per cycle. (3) Dosing/purge times use wrong units and values: article uses 1 s and 20 s; schema requires milliseconds, but the extraction enters 1 and 20 ms instead of 1000 and 20000 ms. (4) Film thickness is incorrect: 0.7 nm was entered (apparently a thickness difference discussed in Fig. 9), not the actual film thickness after 220 cycles; the article provides only relative differences. (5) Many fields are ungrounded or fabricated: uniformity (5%), conformality aspect ratio (1), roughness (0.7 nm, AFM not reported), film density (entered 5.675 with unit g/dm3 while 5.675 g/cm3 was only an assumed bulk value for conversion), elemental concentration (0.5% from IR sensitivity limit, not a measured value), atomic ratio set to 1:19 (this is a cycle ratio, not a measured AES ratio). (6) Device electrical data missing/mis-specified: article reports conductivity ~740 S/cm for case 3 (thus resistivity could be computed), but extraction leaves resistivity None; setting None violates schema typing. (7) ALD system/material mislabeling: materialDeposited is set to ZnO while the extracted process includes Al doping; should be ZnO:Al for doped runs and include Al2O3 in aldMethod. (8) Flow rates are incorrect: article gives total flow 100 sccm, not per-precursor flows; units used (SCM-PER-MIN) are not sccm; purgingGasFlow 10 sccm refers to QCM backside flow, not the process stream. (9) Numerous nulls (None) provided where the schema expects objects/values (e.g., plasmaPower, optical/electrical properties), violating schema constraints against nulls. (10) Supercycle/dosing sequence not fully captured: subcycleSequence ['ZnO','Al2O3'] loses the critical order differences among cases 1–3; separate processes should encode each sequence. Properties to add/review: add separate process entries for each doping case and RD/Z; correct GPC units/values or omit if not reported; correct dosing/purge times in milliseconds; provide accurate film thickness or mark as not reported; revise materialDeposited and aldMethod to include Al2O3; fix flow rate units/values to match article; replace fabricated material properties with traceable values (or omit optional fields); compute resistivity from reported conductivity for case 3; remove None values and ensure all units are QUDT-compliant.
